<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-12-02T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-12-02T00:00:00-05:00" n="654" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d654">
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic"><persName type="from">Mavroyeni Bey</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Translation.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Imperial Legation of Turkey</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-12-02"><hi rend="italic">December 2,
                                1895</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. <hi rend="smallcaps">Secretary of State</hi>: I hasten to send your
                            excellency copy of a telegram I have this instant received from the
                            Sublime Porte: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The American missionaries enjoy throughout the Empire the
                                    greatest protection. Sufficient troops are detailed to guard
                                    them in order to shelter them from the attacks of the Armenian
                                    rioters. Those missionaries have themselves expressed to the
                                    Imperial authorities their gratitude for the protection
                                    accorded.</p>
                            </quote></p>
                        <p>Be pleased, etc.,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Mavroyeni.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>